    <script>
        (function() {
            const minUsers = 10;
            const maxUsers = 2000000;
            
            const colors = {
                low: '#20C997',    
                med: '#FFC52F',    
                high: '#FF9800',   
                critical: '#EA2D2E'
            };

            // Attach to global window object so the inline HTML oninput can find it
            window.updateRiskScale = function(sliderValue) {
                const scale = sliderValue / 100;
                let currentUsers = Math.floor(minUsers * Math.pow((maxUsers / minUsers), scale));
                
                if (currentUsers > 1000) currentUsers = Math.round(currentUsers / 100) * 100;
                if (currentUsers > 100000) currentUsers = Math.round(currentUsers / 1000) * 1000;
                
                document.getElementById('tc-user-count').innerText = currentUsers.toLocaleString('en-US');

                let stateColor, headline, desc, boxBg, nodeCount, animationSpeed;

                if (currentUsers < 10000) {
                    stateColor = colors.low;
                    boxBg = '#E8F5E9'; 
                    headline = "Negligible Risk";
                    desc = "Transactions are sparse. The founders can manually review deposits, manage liquidity, and handle customer support without dedicated governance.";
                    nodeCount = Math.floor(2 + (scale * 20)); 
                    animationSpeed = "4s";
                } 
                else if (currentUsers < 150000) {
                    stateColor = colors.med;
                    boxBg = '#FFF8E1'; 
                    headline = "Operational Strain";
                    desc = "Traffic spikes cause API limits to break. First automated fraud attempts appear. You need dedicated engineers and a compliance officer.";
                    nodeCount = Math.floor(20 + (scale * 40)); 
                    animationSpeed = "2.5s";
                }
                else if (currentUsers < 800000) {
                    stateColor = colors.high;
                    boxBg = '#FFF3E0'; 
                    headline = "Regulatory Scrutiny";
                    desc = "The SEC is watching. You must maintain strict liquidity ratios and submit monthly risk reports. A dedicated Risk Manager is now legally required.";
                    nodeCount = Math.floor(40 + (scale * 60)); 
                    animationSpeed = "1.5s";
                }
                else {
                    stateColor = colors.critical;
                    boxBg = '#FFE0E0'; 
                    headline = "Systemic Complexity";
                    desc = "10,000 withdrawal requests a minute. A single outage affects millions of lives. You cannot survive without an institutional governance structure (11 AVPs).";
                    nodeCount = Math.floor(80 + (scale * 70)); 
                    animationSpeed = "0.7s";
                }

                document.getElementById('tc-vector-count').innerText = nodeCount;
                const statusBox = document.getElementById('tc-risk-status');
                statusBox.style.backgroundColor = boxBg;
                statusBox.style.borderLeftColor = stateColor;
                
                const hl = document.getElementById('tc-status-headline');
                hl.innerText = headline;
                hl.style.color = stateColor;
                
                document.getElementById('tc-status-desc').innerText = desc;

                renderParticles(nodeCount, stateColor, animationSpeed);
            };

            function renderParticles(count, color, speed) {
                const box = document.getElementById('tc-particle-box');
                if (!box) return;
                box.innerHTML = ''; 

                for (let i = 0; i < count; i++) {
                    const node = document.createElement('div');
                    node.className = 'tc-risk-node';
                    
                    const size = Math.floor(Math.random() * 8) + 4;
                    const startX = Math.floor(Math.random() * 100);
                    const startY = Math.floor(Math.random() * 100);
                    const moveX = (Math.random() * 80) - 40;
                    const moveY = (Math.random() * 80) - 40;
                    const delay = Math.random() * 2;

                    node.style.width = size + 'px';
                    node.style.height = size + 'px';
                    node.style.backgroundColor = color;
                    node.style.left = startX + '%';
                    node.style.top = startY + '%';
                    node.style.animationDuration = speed;
                    node.style.animationDelay = '-' + delay + 's';
                    
                    node.style.setProperty('--tx', moveX + 'px');
                    node.style.setProperty('--ty', moveY + 'px');

                    box.appendChild(node);
                }
            }

            // CMS Safe Initialization
            function initTool() {
                if (document.getElementById('tc-risk-slider')) {
                    window.updateRiskScale(0);
                }
            }

            if (document.readyState === 'loading') {
                document.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', initTool);
            } else {
                initTool();
            }
        })();
    </script>
</div>



<p>I was not alone in finding the promotions unusual. Abiola Sowemimo, a fintech human resources executive renowned for helping build Paystack's HR team and practices, told me her first reaction was caution rather than judgment.&nbsp;</p>



<p>"This is unusual. Not that it is automatically wrong, just very unusual," she said. In a company of about 70 people, promoting 11 to AVP at once "would naturally raise questions."&nbsp;</p>



<p>"It is a leadership promotion, so the concern becomes whether this is a real promotion," she added.&nbsp;</p>



<p>But Sowemimo was equally clear that the nature of Cowrywise's business changes the equation. “It looks like an intentional organisational move rather than business as usual,” she said.</p>



<p>Part of what changes the equation is that Cowrywise is regulated by Nigeria's Securities and Exchange Commission (SEC).&nbsp;</p>



<p>A company licensed to manage other people's money faces scrutiny that an ordinary startup does not, because regulators want decision-making distributed among experienced people across important business units like risk, finance, and compliance.</p>



